         <abstract>
            <p>Using the main ideas of Tanaka, the measure-solution {P&lt;sub&gt;t&lt;/sub&gt;}&lt;sub&gt;t&lt;/sub&gt; of a 3-dimensional spatially homogeneous Boltzmann equation of Maxwellian molecules without cutoff is related to a Poisson-driven stochastic differential equation. Using this tool, the convergence to {P&lt;sub&gt;t&lt;/sub&gt;}&lt;sub&gt;t&lt;/sub&gt; of solutions {P&lt;sup&gt;l&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;t&lt;/sub&gt;}&lt;sub&gt;t&lt;/sub&gt; of approximating Boltzmann equations with cutoff is proved. Then, a result of Graham-Meleard is used and allows us to approximate {P&lt;sup&gt;l&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;t&lt;/sub&gt;}&lt;sub&gt;t&lt;/sub&gt; with the empirical measure {Î¼&lt;sup&gt;l,n&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;t&lt;/sub&gt;}&lt;sub&gt;t&lt;/sub&gt; of an easily simulable interacting particle system. Precise rates of convergence are given. A numerical study lies at the end of the paper.</p>
          </abstract>
